{"questionId":"9392","questionHtml":"<p>Find E(<em>T</em>).</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em><strong>METHOD 1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempting to use the expected value formula<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{E}}\\left( X \\right) = \\left( {1 \\times 0.60} \\right) + \\left( {2 \\times 0.30} \\right) + \\left( {3 \\times 0.03} \\right) + \\left( {4 \\times 0.05} \\right) + \\left( {5 \\times 0.02} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>E</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>X</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.60</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.30</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.03</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.05</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.02</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{E}}\\left( X \\right) = 1.59\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>E</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>X</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1.59</mn>\n</math></span>($)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>use of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{E}}\\left( {1.20X + 2.40} \\right) = 1.20{\\text{E}}\\left( X \\right) + 2.40\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>E</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.20</mn>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>2.40</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1.20</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>E</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>X</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2.40</mn>\n</math></span><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{E}}\\left( T \\right) = 1.20\\left( {1.59} \\right) + 2.40\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>E</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>T</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1.20</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.59</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2.40</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = 4.31\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4.31</mn>\n</math></span>($)<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>METHOD 2</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempting to find the probability distribution for <em>T</em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/cd2d3258e79c7b94d9e3b540e0e092f93e297b93.png\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempting to use the expected value formula&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{E}}\\left( T \\right) = \\left( {3.60 \\times 0.60} \\right) + \\left( {4.80 \\times 0.30} \\right) + \\left( {6.00 \\times 0.03} \\right) + \\left( {7.20 \\times 0.05} \\right) + \\left( {8.40 \\times 0.02} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>E</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>T</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3.60</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.60</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4.80</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.30</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>6.00</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.03</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>7.20</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.05</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>8.40</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.02</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = 4.31\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4.31</mn>\n</math></span>($)<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9392","referenceCode":"SPM.2.AHL.TZ0.6a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find E(T).","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.14—Properties of discrete and continuous random variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}